<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">27</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">5</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Sep 1 2007</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">1419</span> - <span property="pageEnd">1431</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17848700/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">17848700</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2007.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Sep 1 2007</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.275065021">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=ACR+%3D+American+College+of+Radiology&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">ACR = American College of Radiology</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=SE+%3D+spin+echo&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">SE = spin echo</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=STIR+%3D+short+inversion+time+inversion+recovery&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">STIR = short inversion time inversion recovery</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">Despite its higher cost, vulnerability to artifacts, and limited availability, MR imaging is feasible and appropriate for the emergent evaluation of selected patients with acute abdominopelvic conditions.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Ajay</span> <span property="familyName">Singh</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Radiology, University of Massachusetts Memorial Medical Center, Worcester, Mass (A.S., R.D.); and Department of Radiology, Massachusetts General Hospital, Boston, Mass (A.S., P.F.H., M.A.B., P.R.M., R.A.N.). Presented as an education exhibit at the 2005 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received March 10, 2006; revision requested May 10 and received January 24, 2007; accepted April 4. P.R.M. is a consultant with Cook Group, Bloomington, Ind; all remaining authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Singh/Ajay" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con2" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Raman</span> <span property="familyName">Danrad</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Radiology, University of Massachusetts Memorial Medical Center, Worcester, Mass (A.S., R.D.); and Department of Radiology, Massachusetts General Hospital, Boston, Mass (A.S., P.F.H., M.A.B., P.R.M., R.A.N.). Presented as an education exhibit at the 2005 RSNA Ann